OL,3,CLast hereditary peers formally leave
OL,4,CHouse of Lords following law change
OL,6,FThe last remaining hereditary peers
OL,7,Fhave sat for the final time ever in
OL,8,Fthe House of Lords.
OL,10,FParliament was formally prorogued on
OL,11,FWednesday afternoon, marking the end
OL,12,Fof hereditary peers in the upper
OL,13,Fchamber.
OL,15,FThe House of Lords (Hereditary Peers)
OL,16,FAct became law earlier this year -
OL,17,Fafter being included in Labour's
OL,18,Fmanifesto commitment - removing all
OL,19,Fhereditary peers' right to speak and
OL,20,Fvote in Parliament by virtue of their
OL,21,Ffamily ties.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
