OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777493189
OL,3,CLast hereditary peers formally leave
OL,4,CHouse of Lords following law change
OL,6,FUnlike members in the House of
OL,7,FCommons, peers in the House of Lords
OL,8,Fare not elected and since 1999, 92
OL,9,Fhereditary peers have been able to sit
OL,10,Fin the Lords and cast their vote.
OL,12,FThose remaining 92 peers are all male
OL,13,Fheirs of aristocratic families whose
OL,14,Fmemberships have been passed down.
OL,16,FBut under the House of Lords
OL,17,F(Hereditary Peers) Act that number has
OL,18,Fbeen effectively reduced to zero.
OL,19,FHowever, several have subsequently
OL,20,Fbeen allowed to continue sitting as
OL,21,Flife peers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
