OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777493189
OL,3,CLast hereditary peers formally leave
OL,4,CHouse of Lords following law change
OL,6,FOfficials previously described the
OL,7,Fcontinued presence of hereditary peers
OL,8,Fin the Lords as "outdated and
OL,9,Findefensible", with reform "long
OL,10,Foverdue and essential".
OL,12,FBut Conservative critics called the
OL,13,Fmove a "vendetta" and "political
OL,14,Fvandalism".
OL,16,FSeven centuries of inherited power
OL,17,Fhave come to an end in the House of
OL,18,FLords: Watch ITV Political
OL,19,FCorrespondent Harry Horton's 2024
OL,20,Freport looking back at the history of
OL,21,Fhereditary peers
