OL,3,CLast hereditary peers formally leave
OL,4,CHouse of Lords following law change
OL,6,FLords Leader Baroness Smith of
OL,7,FBasildon said earlier this year the
OL,8,FAct had "never been about the
OL,9,Fcontribution of individuals, but the
OL,10,Funderlying principle that was agreed
OL,11,Fby Parliament over 25 years ago that
OL,12,Fno one should sit in our Parliament by
OL,13,Fway of an inherited title".
OL,15,FThis means that hereditary peers who
OL,16,Fhave not been made life peers will no
OL,17,Flonger have a right to sit in the
OL,18,FLords now the current parliamentary
OL,19,Fsession has ended.
OL,26,@pD@IOUuD@ZO]
