OL,3,CLast hereditary peers formally leave
OL,4,CHouse of Lords following law change
OL,6,FThe announcement formally ending the
OL,7,Fcurrent parliamentary session was read
OL,8,Fout on behalf of King Charles at a
OL,9,Ftraditional ceremony in the House of
OL,10,FLords on Wednesday afternoon, which
OL,11,Fwas attended by both MPs and peers.
OL,13,FAhead of the prorogation, Lords
OL,14,FSpeaker Lord Forsyth of Drumlean paid
OL,15,Ftribute to those losing their seats on
OL,16,Fthe red benches for their
OL,17,F"distinguished service".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
