OL,3,CLast hereditary peers formally leave
OL,4,CHouse of Lords following law change
OL,6,FMPs, led by Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle,
OL,7,Ffiled out of the Commons after their
OL,8,Fattendance in the upper chamber was
OL,9,Frequested by Black Rod Ed Davis ` the
OL,10,Fsenior officer responsible for
OL,11,Fceremonial protocol.
OL,13,FMPs and peers will return on May 13
OL,14,Ffor the King's Speech, which will set
OL,15,Fout the Government's future
OL,16,Flegislative agenda.
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
